x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.438, Issue.2, p.384 (1985)

x4freetext: Isomeric cross-section ratios in (n,t) reactions on
some medium-and-heavy mass nuclei at 14.6 MeV.
Dynagen neutron generator.
Average energy of the neutrons was 14.6+-0.4 MeV
For all isotopes
.Data taken from NP/A,438,(2),384
Combining the statistical and systematic errors
in quadrature. Major systematic errors due to:
determination of neutron flux via
monitor reactions and
determination of desintegration rates of the products
involving several uncertainties, for example,
uncertainty in efficiencies of the
detectors;
uncertainty in absorption of gamma-rays;
uncertainty in decay data;
uncertainty in chemical yield; etc.
normalization error
